---
import CaseStudyLayout from "../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro";

const meta = [
  { label: "Year", value: "2022" },
  { label: "Client", value: "The Sofa & Chair Company" },
  { label: "Role", value: "Senior Product Designer" },
  { label: "Timeline", value: "12 months" },
];

const stats = [
  { value: "700+", label: "Artboards" },
  { value: "7", label: "Viewports" },
  { value: "12mo", label: "End-to-end build" },
  { value: "1", label: "Sole designer" },
];
---

<CaseStudyLayout
  pageTitle="Larkbury - Sammy Norris"
  meta={meta}
  description="Larkbury London didn't exist before this project. I built it from scratch - brand identity and a fully responsive ecommerce site designed solo across 700+ artboards and seven viewports."
  signoff="Designed at The Sofa & Chair Company"
  signoffYear="2022"
  nextProject={{ title: "Porsche", slug: "porsche" }}
>
  <Fragment slot="title">Larkbury</Fragment>

  <!-- Figure 01 - hero shot -->
  <figure class="figure" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/larkbury/image-larkbury-1-m.jpg" width="2250" height="3000" />
      <img src="/images/projects/larkbury/image-larkbury-1.jpg" alt="Larkbury London brand hero" loading="eager" width="2400" height="1800" />
    </picture>
  </figure>

  <!-- Chapter I - Challenge -->
  <section class="chapter" data-reveal>
    <header class="chapter__head">
      <span class="chapter__num" aria-hidden="true">I.</span>
      <h2 class="chapter__label b2">The challenge</h2>
    </header>

    <blockquote class="chapter__quote">
      The brief was to create a luxury interiors brand from the ground up, and to do it in a way that could hold its own in the high-end market.
    </blockquote>

    <div class="chapter__body">
      <p class="b1">
        The scope covered everything from foundational brand decisions through to a production-ready ecommerce build. Seven viewports meant designing for every context a customer might encounter the brand, ensuring the luxury positioning held whether someone was on a large desktop or a phone.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Figure 02 -->
  <figure class="figure" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/larkbury/image-larkbury-2-m.jpg" width="2250" height="3000" />
      <img src="/images/projects/larkbury/image-larkbury-2.jpg" alt="Larkbury brand and identity work" loading="lazy" width="2400" height="1800" />
    </picture>
  </figure>

  <!-- Chapter II - Process -->
  <section class="chapter" data-reveal>
    <header class="chapter__head">
      <span class="chapter__num" aria-hidden="true">II.</span>
      <h2 class="chapter__label b2">The process</h2>
    </header>

    <h3 class="chapter__h2">
      Seven hundred artboards, <em>one designer.</em>
    </h3>

    <div class="chapter__body">
      <p class="b1">
        I owned the design system first - components, patterns, and tokens that could scale across 700+ artboards without becoming inconsistent. That foundation made it possible to work at pace while keeping the experience coherent across every template, state, and interaction needed for handoff. The design language was deliberately restrained - typography, whitespace, and imagery carry the brand rather than feature density.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Figure 03 -->
  <figure class="figure" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/larkbury/image-larkbury-3-m.jpg" width="2250" height="3000" />
      <img src="/images/projects/larkbury/image-larkbury-3.jpg" alt="Larkbury ecommerce screens" loading="lazy" width="2400" height="1800" />
    </picture>
  </figure>

  <!-- Chapter III - Outcome -->
  <section class="chapter" data-reveal>
    <header class="chapter__head">
      <span class="chapter__num" aria-hidden="true">III.</span>
      <h2 class="chapter__label b2">The outcome</h2>
    </header>

    <h3 class="chapter__h2">
      Restraint <em>doing the heavy lifting.</em>
    </h3>

    <div class="stats">
      {stats.map((s) => (
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat__value">{s.value}</span>
          <span class="stat__label b3">{s.label}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="chapter__body">
      <p class="b1">
        Larkbury London launched and the finished product reflects the ambition of the brief - a brand and digital presence that feels genuinely considered from first touchpoint to last.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Figure 04 -->
  <figure class="figure" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/larkbury/image-larkbury-4-m.jpg" width="2250" height="3000" />
      <img src="/images/projects/larkbury/image-larkbury-4.jpg" alt="Larkbury responsive site" loading="lazy" width="2400" height="1800" />
    </picture>
  </figure>

  <!-- Figure 05 -->
  <figure class="figure" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/larkbury/image-larkbury-5-m.jpg" width="2250" height="3000" />
      <img src="/images/projects/larkbury/image-larkbury-5.jpg" alt="Larkbury detail work" loading="lazy" width="2400" height="1800" />
    </picture>
  </figure>
</CaseStudyLayout>
